'''The Piedmont Environmental Council''' (PEC) is a [[Virginia]]-based [[charitable organization|charitable]] [[environmental organization]] headquartered in [[Warrenton, Virginia]], [[United States]]. PEC's mission is to promote and protect the [[Piedmont region of Virginia|Piedmont area]]'s rural economy, natural resources, history, and beauty. The organization was founded in 1972.
PEC's service territory includes [[Albemarle County, Virginia|Albemarle County]], [[Clarke County, Virginia|Clarke County]], [[Culpeper County, Virginia|Culpeper County]], [[Fauquier County, Virginia|Fauquier County]], [[Greene County, Virginia|Greene County]], [[Loudoun County, Virginia|Loudoun County]], [[Madison County, Virginia|Madison County]], [[Orange County, Virginia|Orange County]], [[Rappahannock County, Virginia|Rappahannock County]] and the [[Charlottesville, Virginia|City of Charlottesville]].
