'''San Martín Texmelucan de Labastida''' is a city in the west-central part of the state of [[Puebla]] in [[Mexico]], adjacent to the southwest corner of the state of [[Tlaxcala]]. It is the municipal seat of the [[municipalities of Mexico|municipality]] of [[San Martín Texmelucan (municipality)|San Martín Texmelucan]]. The city is the fifth largest in the state of Puebla, with a 2005 census population of 135500 inhabitants.

On December 19, 2010, an oil pipeline at a [[Petroleos Mexicanos]] (Pemex) pumping station in the city exploded, killing at least 27 people and injuring more than 50. 32 houses were destroyed and several times that many damaged.<ref name=latimes22_12/> The explosion is believed to have been caused by attempts to puncture the pipe to steal oil.<ref name=latimes22_12>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/world/la-fg-1220-mexico-oil-explosion-20101220,0,5059943.story|title=27 die in oil pipeline explosion in Mexico|author=Ellingwood, Ken |work=The Los Angeles Times|date=December 20, 2010|accessdate=December 22, 2010}}</ref>

